      <bioghist altrender="biography" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
         <head>Biography</head>
         <p>
            <persname>Chester D. Jarvis</persname> (<date>1876-1948</date>) was a horticulturist who worked at the <corpname>Connecticut Agricultural College</corpname> from <date>1906-1915</date>. He began in the <corpname>Agricultural Experiment Station</corpname> and was  later named director of the reorganized Extension Service in 1913. Jarvis served in the  latter capacity until 1915 when he became a specialist in Agricultural Education for the  Department of Agriculture.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>The <persname>Chester D. Jarvis</persname> Papers consist of the professional  correspondence of Jarvis during the dates 1909-1913. The papers cover a wide range of topics, including job offers from competing institutions, a department automobile purchase, lecture topics, and budgetary matters. Forty-three of the approximately 120 letters are between Jarvis and college president <persname>Charles L. Beach</persname>. An  undated copy of the first annual report of the Extension Service is located in folder  6.</p>
      </scopecontent>
